snippet.textDisplay:
When my dad met an old friend, he drank a little and started talking about those old green days, but after a while, when they started singing this song, my head would get hot, I didn't understand or didn't want to understand the meaning of this song. My father was born on 1924 in Rangpur district of present-day Bangladesh😊. When our country was divided in 1947, he fled to India.  Dad is passed away on 31/05/2019😢.When I started thinking that I had hurt my father's thoughts, my eyes kept watering and nothing wanted to stop, but now I have understood myself, so I have lost that person as well as apologizing. I apologize to whom I'm asking😢. Please forgive me if I made a big mistake😢. It was great to hear this song again today at Coke Studio.
Thank you so much #Coke Studio ❤from Assam
